#Text=Dover ( New Hampshire )
#Text=Dover is a city in New Hampshire , United States .
#Text=Settled in 1623 , it
#Text=pre-dates the founding of America and is the 7th oldest city in the country .
#Text=By car
#Text=Dover is located off of the Spaulding Turnpike ( Route 16 ) , and is about 10 minutes from I-95 , which connects to Maine and Massachusetts .
#Text=By train

#Text=Dover is served by Amtrak via multiple daily Downeaster trains , running between Boston and Portland , Maine , with some continuing to Brunswick . is located a block west of downtown , at the intersection of Third Street and Chestnut Street , next to St. Mary 's church .
#Text=During the summer , the Downeaster makes an additional stop at Old Orchard Beach , near to the resorts between Dover and Portland .
#Text=This comes in handy on summer weekends , when I-95 and US-1 are both bumper to bumper with vacation traffic .
#Text=By bus
#Text=Wildcat Transit , operated by the University of New Hampshire , runs from many points in Dover to the campus , and connecting buses can be taken to Portsmouth and Newington .
#Text=COAST bus is the local , non-university bus company .
#Text=The Dover school district uses four COAST buses in addition to the normal yellow school buses to transport high school students , and several COAST stops are for this purpose only .
#Text=C&J Trailways operates hourly service every day from Boston 's South Station , with some buses continuing on to Logan International Airport .

#Text=All buses go at least as far north as the bus terminal at Pease International Tradeport ( accessible from the Spaulding Turnpike and I-95 ) , with about half continuing on to the Dover train station .
#Text=All C&J buses make an intermediate stop in Newburyport , Massachusetts .
#Text=See
#Text=Woodman Institute Museum , 182 Central Av , ☏ +1 603-742-1038 .
#Text=W - Su 12:30PM-4:30PM ; closed Dec-Mar .
#Text=Dover 's only history , science and art museum offers interesting insect and geological specimens as well as local historic memorabilia .
#Text=Three buildings open for tours including a 1675 colonial garrison house with artifacts .
#Text=Reservations requested for groups .
#Text=Childrens Museum of New Hampshire , 6 Washington St. , ☏ +1603 742-2002 .
#Text=The Children 's Museum operates exclusively for charitable purposes and serves as an educational resource for schools , families and communities .
#Text=The museum strives to support the diverse population of the region , to provide learning opportunities for all children , and to enrich the services of regional schools .
#Text=The Children 's Museum of New Hampshire offers a variety of programs for children from preschool through middle school .
#Text=From science classes to overnights , museum educators have designed engaging , high-quality programs that feature hands-on opportunities for learning while having fun .
#Text=Do
#Text=William Damm Garrison House , 182 Central Ave , ☏ +1 603-742-1038 .
#Text=Built in 1675 , creak up the narrow ladder steps to the second floor loft and wonder how someone like you could have lived there and slept in those old rope beds .
#Text=The Woodman is a true turn of the century natural history , local history and art museum established in 1916 .
#Text=See an entire floor dedicated to taxidermist stuffed animals .
#Text=This includes an enormous 10-foot polar bear .
#Text=Visit the Senator John P. Hale home and hear the story about his young daughter Lucy and an actor by the name of Booth .
#Text=The Woodman is an experience you wo n't want to miss .
#Text=Call for special group tours .
#Text=Buy
#Text=Images of the Past Gallery , 35 Atkinson St , ☏ +1 603-742-7783 .
#Text=Historic framed photographs of Dover and the seacoast areas reproduced from original glass plate negatives . By appointment .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Dover divides its restaurant ' areas ' mainly into two distinct locations .
#Text=In north Dover , off Spaulding Tpke 's exit 9 , are a plethora of chain restaurants .
#Text=Landing in this area you will find Chili 's , Uno 's , Applebee 's , Subway , McDonalds , Wendy 's , and Amato 's ( although the latter is Somersworth ) .
#Text=A short drive south on Central Avenue will bring you to the old mill area of the city .
#Text=This is an area of more the one-of-a-kind custom restaurants .
#Text=Each has a unique style and atmosphere that covers a very wide variety and one of them is sure to please your taste for the evening .
#Text=In this area the street addresses range from 286 Central Ave up into the 300 's .
#Text=Dos Amigos , 286 Central Ave , ☏ +1603 834-6494 .
#Text=Low-cost , high-quality tacos , burritos and other Mexican fare .
#Text=Their sweet potato tacos are especially worth trying .
#Text=La Festa Brick and Brew , 300 Central Ave , ☏ +1603 743-4100 .
#Text=Exceptional creative and traditional pizzas .
#Text=Blue Latitudes , 431 Central Ave ( inside the Cocheco Falls Millworks ) , ☏ +1603 750-4222 .
#Text=Fantastic dining in the heart of downtown Dover .
#Text=Excellent menu , staff is polite and attentive .
#Text=The bar is a perfect spot for couples on a night out or groups looking to get away from the usual spot .
#Text=The lamb is succulent , the steak tips , always a treat .
#Text=Drink
#Text=Cara Irish Pub , 11 4th St , ☏ +1 603-343-4390 .

#Text=Free evening appetizers and drinks as well as hot breakfast daily . 115 .

#Text=New all-suite hotel .
#Text=Rooms include kitchen with full-size refrigerator , microwave , two-burner stove and dishwasher .
#Text=Free internet , voice mail , free hot breakfast daily . $ 125 .
#Text=The Silver Fountain Inn , 103 Silver St , toll-free : +1-888-548-6888 .
#Text=An elegant bed & breakfast in a historic Victorian mansion .
#Text=Many of the home 's Victorian details have been preserved ; the house is quite stunning .
#Text=The Garrison Hotel , 200 Sterling Way , ☏ +1 ( 603 ) 842-6783 .
